The paper discusses the development of a semi-supervised learning algorithm for deep learning, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The algorithm is tested on image datasets, which suggests that it may also fall under the categories of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the practical applicability of the algorithm, which suggests that it may fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
